        "title": "Your Skin Looks Flat and Lifeless in Photos",
        "body_text": "<p>You look fine in the mirror at home. But someone takes a photo at dinner or your daughter tags you on social media, and you barely recognise yourself. Your skin looks dull, matte, almost grey. The life has been sucked out of your face.</p><p>Traditional foundations create a flat, opaque layer on the surface of your skin. They block the natural light that gives your face dimension and warmth. On mature skin, where volume has already started to change, this flat finish can add years rather than subtract them.</p><p>The foundations that photograph well on women over 50 work differently. They allow light to pass through and reflect off your actual skin tone underneath, creating the kind of natural luminosity that reads as healthy and youthful — in person and on camera.</p>",
        "link_text": "",
        "link_type": "anchor",
        "link_anchor": "",
