        "title": "You're Touching Up More Than Once a Day",
        "body_text": "<p>If your foundation routine includes a midday mirror check, a pressed powder compact in your bag, or a full reapplication before evening plans — that's not normal maintenance. That's your product failing you.</p><p>Foundations that require constant touch-ups are typically oxidising on your skin. They react with your skin's natural oils and pH, causing the shade to shift — usually darker or more orange — throughout the day. You're not \"wearing it off.\" The formula is literally changing colour on your face.</p><p>A foundation built for mature skin should work with your skin chemistry, not against it. The right formula stays true to your shade from morning to evening, without oxidation, without fading, and without you thinking about it.</p>",
        "link_text": "",
