        "title": "Your Shade Looks Wrong in Different Lighting",
        "body_text": "<p>It matched perfectly in the shop. But under the fluorescent lights at the office, it looks pink. In natural light, it pulls orange. By evening, the person in the mirror is wearing a shade that doesn't belong on your face.</p><p>This is one of the most common frustrations women over 50 describe, and it's not because they picked the wrong shade. It's because traditional foundations use static pigments — a single fixed colour that was mixed in a lab. Your skin, on the other hand, has complex undertones that shift depending on blood flow, temperature, and the light you're standing in.</p><p>The solution isn't finding a \"better match.\" It's finding a foundation with intelligent pigment technology that adapts to your skin's unique tone in real time — so it looks right in every room, at every hour, without you having to own six different shades.</p>",
