        "title": "You've Stopped Wearing Foundation Altogether",
        "body_text": "<p>This is the one that matters most. If you've opened your makeup drawer, stared at the lineup of foundations that didn't work, and decided it's just not worth the effort anymore — you're not alone. Thousands of women over 50 have quietly walked away from foundation because every option either caked, creased, oxidised, or made them look worse.</p><p>But here's the truth: foundation didn't fail you. The formulas you were using were never designed for your skin in the first place. They were designed for 25-year-olds and repackaged with a \"mature skin\" label.</p><p>A new generation of foundations built specifically for women over 50 are changing that. They use tone-adapting pigment technology that adjusts to your unique skin tone, lightweight formulas that don't settle into lines, and skincare-grade ingredients that actually improve your skin while you wear them. The women who've tried them aren't just coming back to foundation — they're saying it's the best their skin has ever looked.</p>",
